text:
Hello there; I have a custom code in the footer of my email template. When I send a Marketing Email Preview, the text is White per specification. When I send a "real email," the text is blue. The custom code is overwritten by the email template code. Do you have any idea on how to overcome this? Here is my custom code :

&lt;style&gt;
.thematic a, a:active, a:visited {
text-decoration: none;
color: #FFFFFF;
}

&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;div style="margin: 0 auto; text-align: center; color: #FFFFFF !important; font-family: 'Roboto', Sans-serif; font-weight: bold;"&gt;

&lt;div class="thematic" style="text-align: left; padding: 5px; width: 70px; margin: 2px auto; height: 70px; background-color: #005CB8 !important; display: inline-grid; font-size: .75em"&gt;&lt;a href=<https://asef.org/themes/culture/>&gt;Culture&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="thematic" style="text-align: left; padding: 5px; width: 70px; margin: 2px auto; height: 70px; background-color: #FFA388 !important; display: inline-grid; font-size: .75em"&gt;&lt;a href=<https://asef.org/themes/economy/>&gt;Economy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
